# Template for the local-stream `.env` at the repo root.
# Copy to `.env` and fill in real values; `.env` is gitignored.
#
# Loaded by:
#   - `scripts/run_local_stream.py` via `dotenv.load_dotenv()` so plain
#     `os.environ.get(...)` (e.g. the TURN code) sees the values.
#   - `avaturn_live_streamer.settings.Config` via pydantic-settings' `env_file=`.
#
# See README §6 "Local Stream" for the full walkthrough.


# --- Conversation engine -----------------------------------------------------

# OpenAI Realtime API key (the streamer mints short-lived client secrets from
# this; never sent to the browser). Required for the `openai` engine.
OPENAI__API_KEY=""

# Cartesia (optional alternative to OpenAI). Required for the `cartesia` engine.
# CARTESIA_API_KEY=""
# CARTESIA_AGENT_ID=""


# --- WebRTC ICE / TURN (optional) --------------------------------------------
#
# All variables in this section are OPTIONAL. ICE tries direct UDP first
# (host + STUN-reflexive candidates) and only falls back to a TURN relay if
# direct fails — which only happens when the network in between can't pass
# UDP between browser and streamer (typical: streamer on a cloud VM whose
# security group blocks inbound UDP). On a laptop / LAN setup you can leave
# all of these unset.
#
# The in-browser connectivity card surfaces the verdict and points here if
# TURN is actually needed. See README §6 "TURN server setup" for the
# walkthrough.

# Cloudflare Realtime TURN credentials. The streamer mints short-lived
# per-session TURN credentials from these; the long-lived API token never
# leaves the server.
# CLOUDFLARE_TURN_KEY_ID=""
# CLOUDFLARE_TURN_KEY_TOKEN=""

# Alternative: a standard TURN server (self-hosted coturn, etc.). When set,
# takes precedence over Cloudflare.
# TURN_URL="turn:turn.example.com:3478"
# TURN_USERNAME=""
# TURN_CREDENTIAL=""

# STUN server override. Defaults to Google's public STUN.
# STUN_URL="stun:stun.l.google.com:19302"
